# Localskills Provider

The Localskills provider is used to manage resources on [localskills.sh](https://localskills.sh), a multi-tenant skill sharing platform. With this provider you can define skills and rules, publish versioned content, manage teams and membership, issue API tokens, configure OIDC trust policies for CI/CD pipelines, and set up enterprise SAML SSO and SCIM provisioning -- all as Terraform-managed infrastructure.

Use this provider to codify your organization's skill library and access controls. Teams can collaborate on shared skills while Terraform ensures that configuration stays consistent, auditable, and reproducible across environments.

