## Authentication

The provider requires an API token to authenticate with the localskills.sh API. Tokens follow the format `lsk_` followed by 64 hexadecimal characters.

You can obtain a token from your localskills.sh account settings or by creating one with the `localskills_user_token` or `localskills_team_token` resources.

The recommended approach is to set the `LOCALSKILLS_API_TOKEN` environment variable:

```sh
export LOCALSKILLS_API_TOKEN="lsk_your_token_here"
```

Alternatively, you can set the `api_token` attribute directly in the provider block. Avoid hard-coding tokens in version-controlled files; use Terraform variables or a secrets manager instead.

The `base_url` defaults to `https://localskills.sh` and can be overridden with the `LOCALSKILLS_BASE_URL` environment variable or the `base_url` provider attribute for self-hosted or staging environments.

